FORT MYERS — The Rays play the second half of their spring-opening Fort Myers doubleheader today, facing the Red Sox at 1:05 p.m., with radio coverage on WDAE and the team network. Top prospect Taj Bradley will be on the mound for the Rays, likely working just one inning. Several familiar names will make their springs debuts, including outfielders Jose Siri, catcher Christian Bethancourt and first baseman Jonathan Aranda. Top position prospect Curtis Mead will be the DH. The Rays lost their opener 8-4 to the Twins on Saturday as they got adjusted to the new rules, with only one shift violation called. Here is the Rays lineup: And for the Red Sox: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.